    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device with medium model influence. Primary validation result (RH index at nominal operating point) demonstrates normalised error of 2.5% against experimental data, well within the 5% acceptance criterion. Pressure-head validation confirms hydraulic fidelity across the operating range. The worst-case envelope assessment supports the design decision with high engineering confidence. Assurance level is declared High reflecting the depth of the mesh-independence study, the dual-QoI validation coverage, and the sponsor's mature simulation program governance. The package is accepted for submission to support 510(k) predicate comparison.",
